      "TN-C-S systems combine neutral and earth in the supply but separate them at the intake.",
      "ADS relies on a continuous path for fault current to reach the protective device.",
      "The CPC serves the individual circuit, while the earthing conductor connects the whole installation to the means of earthing."
    ],
    "questionText": "A new domestic installation is connected to a PME (Protective Multiple Earthing) supply. Identify the specific three-letter earthing system code for this arrangement and explain the distinct roles that the CPC and the Earthing Conductor play in the ADS process when a fault occurs on a kitchen socket circuit.",
