      "TN-C-S",
      "The CPC (Circuit Protective Conductor) carries the fault current from the specific circuit (kitchen socket) to the main earthing terminal.",
      "The Earthing Conductor provides the main link between the installation's earthing terminal and the supplier's earth/neutral point.",
      "Together they create the path that allows the protective device to trip."
    ],
    "hint": "Think about the acronym for 'Combined' then 'Separate'. For the conductors, distinguish between the one inside the twin and earth cable and the one that connects the whole house to the street supply."
  }
}

